    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped red onion</strong> to the dish with the <strong>sliced carrot</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [750ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat – this is your <strong>meat-free mince ragù</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
